        <h3>Associations and YMCA</h3>
        <p class="par-lg">Seton being the heart of the largest YMCA in Calgary, the prospective association of Seton homeowners and the Union Parks are all associations with specialized programs to make sure you never get bored all year round. The YMCA has locations that cut across different parts of the city. Since 1902, the YMCA has provided Calgarians with exciting recreational activities and health programs. Additionally, there's the Brooklyn Residential YMCA with a 330,000 sq ft facility close to South Health Campus. With a variety of amenities, no doubt you'll love Seton.</p>

        <h3>More Room for Development</h3>
        <p class="par-lg">Regardless of whatever level you might be in, there's more room for growth and advancement as there is a wider variety of places you can work, school, play, learn, connect with people.</p>

        <h3>Lower Cost of Living</h3>
        <p class="par-lg">Compared to some communities in Calgary, including Alberta, Seton has a lower cost of living; the cost of living is up to 5% lower than Alberta.</p>

        <h3>Lower Crime Rate</h3>
        <p class="par-lg">You can enjoy living in this community as it has a lower total crime rate when compared with Alberta; the crime rate is up to 38% lower.</p>

        <h3>Higher Household Income</h3>
        <p class="par-lg">Seton has an incredibly higher employment household income of up to 19 percent higher than Alberta.</p>

        <h3>Great Seton Restaurants</h3>
        <p class="par-lg">There are a variety of restaurants, especially the ones with exquisite services like Starbelly. From the eclectic scenery and exciting food choices to the unique list of cocktails and heart-welcoming staff, there is no reason why you shouldn't love restaurants in Seton.</p>

        <h3>Movie Theater</h3>
        <p class="par-lg">The Cineplex Cinema in Seton offers a fantastic movie experience where you can watch your favorite character. It has a 3D screen and a DBOX screen where you can feel the motion of the movie. Private viewing isn't left out as there are VIP rooms for people who love privacy.</p>

        <h3>MEC Calgary South</h3>
        <p class="par-lg">For lovers of outdoor activities, MEC is one place to check out definitely. If you're a camper, biker, or hiker, the MEC store is ready to supply your gear needs from head to toe. The store offers various options such as class options, workshops, meetups, and bike shops.</p>

        <h3>South Health Campus</h3>
        <p class="par-lg">There's nothing more convenient than having quick and easy access to pediatric care for your kids. As more and more people are moving to Seton to build their lives with their families, it's not unusual that there would be a higher demand for pediatric care. The South Health Campus has a general pediatric clinic that provides quality care and amazing services to the young ones.</p>

